  "prompt": "What should I do to get more answers of my questions from Quora?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to get more answers on Quora:\n\n1. Ask clear and specific questions\n- Be precise about what you want to know\n- Use proper grammar and spelling\n- Provide context and necessary details\n\n2. Write detailed questions\n- Explain your background or reasoning\n- Add relevant context\n- Make the question engaging\n\n3. Use good formatting\n- Break up text with paragraphs\n- Use bullet points if needed\n- Make the question easy to read\n\n4. Choose the right topics and categories\n- Tag your question appropriately\n- Select relevant topics\n- Target areas where experts are active\n\n5. Promote engagement\n- Use an interesting title\n- Add images or visual elements\n- Make the question conversational\n\n6. Follow up and interact\n- Thank people who answer\n- Upvote helpful responses\n- Comment and ask follow-up questions\n\n7. Be patient\n- Good answers take time\n- Don't expect immediate responses\n- Allow time for experts to see and respond\n\n8. Improve your own Quora profile\n- Have a complete profile\n- Follow relevant topics\n- Provide quality answers to others' questions\n\n9. Share your question on social media\n- Increase visibility\n- Attract more potential answerers\n\nThese strategies can help you get more and better answers on Quora.",
